---
const tags = ['Product design', 'System design', 'AI as system layer'];
---

<section class="hero" aria-label="Introduction">
  <div class="container-site hero__inner">
    <ul class="hero__label animate-fade-up" aria-label="Practice areas">
      {tags.map((tag, i) => (
        <li class="hero__tag">
          <span class="hero__tag-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          {tag}
          {i < tags.length - 1 && <span class="hero__sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>}
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>

    <h1 class="hero__headline animate-fade-up animate-delay-100">
      I build systems that<br />make complex things <em>usable</em>.
    </h1>

    <p class="hero__paragraph animate-fade-up animate-delay-200">
      I design and build product systems end to end. Most of the work lives
      inside long-running platforms where structure and consistency actually
      matter, and the design problem is usually the constraint, not the canvas.
    </p>

    <p class="hero__paragraph hero__paragraph--secondary animate-fade-up animate-delay-300">
      More recently, that work has stretched into AI-native products,
      where the model is one constrained stage in a structured pipeline
      and prompt engineering is part of the system, not the chat.
    </p>

    <div class="hero__ctas animate-fade-up animate-delay-400">
      <a
        href="/build"
        class="hero__cta hero__cta--primary"
        data-track="cta_click"
        data-track-cta="see-the-work"
        data-track-loc="home-hero"
      >
        See the work
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="hero__cta hero__cta--ghost"
        data-track="cta_click"
        data-track-cta="get-in-touch"
        data-track-loc="home-hero"
      >Get in touch</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    /* Header is 60px on mobile, 64 on desktop. Keep generous breathing room
       without dominating the first viewport. CTAs at the bottom now provide
       visual closure, so the desktop top padding can be tighter than the
       headline-only original — 240px+160px left an empty band above the
       label that read as dead space, not breathing room. */
    padding-top: calc(60px + var(--space-12));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .hero {
      padding-top: calc(64px + var(--space-16));
      padding-bottom: var(--space-20);
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hero {
      padding-top: calc(64px + var(--space-20));
      padding-bottom: var(--space-24);
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .hero {
      padding-top: calc(64px + 112px);
      padding-bottom: 128px;
    }
  }

  .hero__inner {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .hero__label {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px 8px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hero__label {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    }
  }

  .hero__tag {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    line-height: 1.4;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  @media (min-width: 380px) {
    .hero__tag {
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    }
  }

  .hero__tag-dot {
    width: 4px;
    height: 4px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .hero__sep {
    color: var(--color-border);
    margin-left: 8px;
  }

  .hero__headline {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(38px, 9.5vw, 92px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.04;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    max-width: 15ch;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hero__headline {
      line-height: 1.02;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    }
  }

  .hero__headline em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .hero__paragraph {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 18px);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    opacity: 0.94;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hero__paragraph {
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
  }

  .hero__paragraph--secondary {
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: 0;
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .hero__ctas {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px 12px;
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hero__ctas {
      margin-top: var(--space-10);
      gap: 12px 16px;
    }
  }

  .hero__cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 8px;
    min-height: 48px;
    padding: 0 22px;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: transform 200ms var(--ease-out), background-color 200ms, border-color 200ms, color 200ms, box-shadow 200ms;
    -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
  }

  .hero__cta--primary {
    background-color: var(--color-text);
    color: var(--color-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-text);
  }

  .hero__cta--primary:hover {
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.14);
  }

  .hero__cta--ghost {
    background-color: transparent;
    color: var(--color-text);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .hero__cta--ghost:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background-color: var(--color-accent-dim);
  }

  /* Stretch buttons full-width on the smallest screens for thumb-friendly hits */
  @media (max-width: 380px) {
    .hero__ctas {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
    }
    .hero__cta {
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
